  "texts": [
    "It can be seen from Figure 11 that the values of R STD Hα /R EXT Hα of the normal distribution model (data points in light gray) have a decreasing trend with the increase of N obs, and vary from about 0.50 (corresponding to smaller N obs) to about 0.15 (corresponding to larger N obs).",
    "The distribution of the R STD Hα /R EXT Hα values of the MRS sample (data points in blue) is generally consistent with the simulated distribution of the normal distribution model.",
    "In order to examine the degree of consistency and possible discrepancies between the R STD Hα /R EXT Hα distributions of the MRS sample and the normal distribution model, in Figures 12a and 12d the probability density of the medium and large R STD Hα /R EXT Hα values of the MRS sample is higher than that of the normal distribution model.",
    "This is true for both the N obs = 3 and N obs = 4 subsamples.",
    "The normal distribution model represents random fluctuation of Hα activity; the discrepancies of the R STD Hα /R EXT Hα distribution of the MRS sample from that of the normal distribution model mean that at lease part of the stellar sources in the MRS sample have regular variations of Hα activity instead of random fluctuations."
